  "plan": "- Design a central server application (software) for access control, user management, and logging, interacting with individual door lock units.\n- Develop a door unit with a microcontroller (e.g., ESP32 for WiFi, or an STM32 with an Ethernet module) to communicate with the server and control the electric strike.\n- Integrate an RFID/NFC reader or a Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) module for proximity sensing of registered devices at each door unit.\n- Use an electric strike (actuator) controlled by a relay module connected to the microcontroller, along with a door position sensor (e.g., magnetic reed switch) for tracking.\n- Design custom 3D-printed enclosures for the door unit's electronics, ensuring secure mounting near the door frame and accommodating the electric strike wiring.\n- Implement power supply units (e.g., 12V DC) for each electric strike and the associated microcontroller, with consideration for backup power.",
